-- =============================================
-- ARCHITECT'S DESIGN NOTES
-- =============================================

-- NULL handling
--   Customers 3, 4, 6, 9, 11 (email missing)
--   Customers 4, 6, 11 (phone missing)
--   Support Tickets 2, 3, 6, 7, 9, 11, 12, 15 (resolved_date NULL)
--   Enables IS NULL / IS NOT NULL exercises

-- KYC Status
--   Pending: Customers 3, 12
--   Verified: Customers 1, 2, 4, 5, 7, 8, 10, 11
--   Rejected: Customer 9
--   Incomplete: Customer 6
--   Enables status-based filtering

-- Risk Scores
--   Low: Customers 1, 2, 4, 7, 10
--   Medium: Customers 3, 5, 8, 11
--   High: Customers 6, 9, 12
--   Enables logical operator and IN exercises

-- Account Types
--   Savings, Current, Salary, Joint
--   Enables category-based filtering

-- Transaction Types
--   Payment, Debit, Credit, Transfer
--   Enables IN and BETWEEN exercises

-- Card Status
--   Active, Blocked, Expired, Lost
--   Enables status-based filtering

-- Loan Status
--   Active, Completed, Defaulted, Pending
--   Enables logical operator exercises

-- Ticket Status
--   Open, In Progress, Resolved, Closed
--   Enables status-based filtering

-- Fraud Flags
--   Transaction 53 is flagged as fraud (is_fraud = 1)
--   Enables fraud detection exercises

-- Date Spread
--   Transactions and loans spread across Q1‑Q3 2025
--   Enables BETWEEN date range exercises

-- Multiple Payments per Loan
--   Loan 1 has 5 payments
--   Loan 2 has 4 payments
--   Loan 3 has 3 payments
--   Loan 4 has 2 payments
--   Loan 5 has 2 payments
--   Loan 6 has 2 payments
--   Enables aggregation (GROUP BY, SUM, COUNT) in Module 3

-- Self-Join Readiness
--   Employees table has manager_id
--   Enables SELF JOIN in Module 4

-- Multi-Table JOINS
--   Customers → Accounts → Transactions → Merchants
--   Customers → Accounts → Cards
--   Customers → Loans → Loan Payments
--   Customers → Support Tickets → Employees
--   Employees → Branches
--   Enables all JOIN types in Module 4

-- Business Stakeholders
--   Each table supports a department:
